Now I started counting how many moves it takes to queen my e pawn. In my mind it went like this: 32. e5 Rxa2 33. e6 Re2 34. e7 b5 35. Rc8+ and winning. Naturally that is if White plays horribly. White always has 34. ... Be8 but even then it ties up his Bishop and Rook guarding my dangerous e pawn. Naturally black has a far superior continuation as we see in the game.
